<br>
Question is do I want to wear it?<br>
<br>
My character is a lvl 46 druid currently wearing a chrysobali (sp) talisman +3 wis +20 mana.  With the tailsman she is at 201 wis.  I'm not sure of the wis/mana converting formulas.  And does her wis help her with anything else casting wise other than mana (resists, fizzles ect.)<br>
<br>
Ndainye of Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/18/01 3:20:10 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velium Black Sapphire Necklace</span><hr size=1> Wisdom only affects how much mana you have as far as I know.  At level 50, 1 wis = 10 mana.  The mana per wis goes down below fifty and up after it to 12 mana at 60.  For ease of math we will assume level 50.<br>
<br>
Chrysobal talisman = 3 wis (30 mana) + 20 mana. = 50 mana.<br>
Velium Black Saph = 65 hp/mana<br>
<br>
With the velium black saph neclace you pick up 15 mana and 65 hp so it seems like a good trade to me.<br>
<br>
Since your wisdom is 201 you will only have a 198 wisdom, but your mana pool will be slightly bigger.  If you can pick up another 2 wisdom somewhere else, you will be able to net 35 mana and 65 hp from the swap.<br>
<br>
If you trade skill, I'd keep your talisman though because the higher of wis/int (in this case probably wis) governs your rate of skill ups in a trade skill.  And this isn't limited at 200 like mana is.<br>
<br>
In summary go with the black sapphire neclace. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
